<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="475" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,510,931]" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,510,535]" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. In the group V key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier" box="[599,802,510,535]" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1964) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part II. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Aphiochaeta. Studia Entomologica, 7, 257 - 416." type="journal article" year="1964">
Borgmeier (
<number box="[734,794,510,535]" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[814,982,511,534]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seaverorum">
<emphasis box="[814,982,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">M. seaverorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys to 
<taxonomicName authority="Borgmeier." authorityName="Borgmeier." box="[1076,1400,510,535]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subnudifemur">
<emphasis box="[1076,1267,510,534]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">M. subnudifemur</emphasis>
Borgmeier.
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seaverorom">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">M. seaverorom</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from this species (and a majority of other species in the genus) by the unique, wedge shaped structure of its cerci, which each have 
<number box="[746,774,583,607]" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" value="10.0">10</number>
+ setae (
<figureCitation box="[869,953,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 87 – 92" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[167,1419,255,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[150,1436,241,1829]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 87 – 92. Male genitalia, left lateral. 87. Megaselia rodriguezorum. 88. Megaselia sacatelensis. 89. Megaselia seaverorum. 90. Megaselia sidneyae. 91. Megaselia steptoeae. 92. Megaselia wiegmanae." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/242988/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="475">
Fig. 
<number box="[921,953,583,607]" pageId="24" pageNumber="475" value="89.0">89</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
